WEBVTT

00:02.086 --> 00:05.171
- Here's what you missed
last week. Quinn's pregnant.
- You're off the Cheerios.

00:05.255 --> 00:07.674
Everyone thinks
Finn's the father.
Though really, it's Puck.

00:07.758 --> 00:10.259
But Quinn thinks
he's a Lima loser and doesn't
want anything to do with him.

00:10.344 --> 00:12.804
- What's up, MILF?
- Also, Kurt told everybody
he's gay,

00:12.888 --> 00:15.515
including his dad,
who was actually cool about it.

00:15.599 --> 00:17.392
- Thanks for telling me, Kurt.
- And that's what
you missed on—

00:17.476 --> 00:19.477
♪ Glee ♪

00:20.479 --> 00:22.438
[Whistle Blows]

00:24.650 --> 00:26.442
[Whistle Blows]

00:30.114 --> 00:32.907
[Girl]
Five, six, seven!

00:32.991 --> 00:35.034
Five, six, seven!

00:36.578 --> 00:39.956
Five, six, seven!
One, two, three, four!

00:40.040 --> 00:42.041
Five, six, seven!

00:43.335 --> 00:45.336
Five, six, seven, eight!

00:48.173 --> 00:50.466
You shouldn't
do this to yourself.

00:50.551 --> 00:52.552
Do what?

00:53.804 --> 00:56.347
I know how much it hurts
to be off the team.

00:56.432 --> 00:58.516
You're just torturing
yourself watching.

00:59.601 --> 01:02.228
I need
a good distraction.

01:02.354 --> 01:04.647
From what?
[Sighs]

01:12.948 --> 01:17.910
$685?
That's how much
a sonogram costs.

01:17.995 --> 01:19.912
This is just
the beginning.

01:19.997 --> 01:22.415
There's gonna be
more doctors' visits,

01:22.499 --> 01:25.376
vitamins, new clothes
for when I explode.

01:25.461 --> 01:27.587
[Sighs]
What are we gonna do?

01:27.671 --> 01:29.422
What are you gonna do?

01:29.506 --> 01:32.925
Well, I'm looking for a job.
I mean, no one's hiring.

01:33.010 --> 01:36.637
I almost got in at Olive Garden,
but they said I was too tall
to be a busboy.

01:36.722 --> 01:40.600
Somewhere in that
pea brain of yours...

01:40.684 --> 01:42.602
is a man.

01:42.686 --> 01:47.356
Access him and tell him to prove
to me that I chose the right guy
to have a baby with.

01:47.441 --> 01:49.358
I will.

01:49.443 --> 01:53.488
I'll-I'll find a job.
You can count on me, I swear.

01:53.572 --> 01:56.449
- Where-Where are you goin'?
- You were right.

01:56.575 --> 01:59.577
[Whistle Continues Blowing]
This does hurt too much.

02:03.874 --> 02:06.292
My blog has lit up
with comments suggesting...

02:06.376 --> 02:09.295
you don't have
a shot at nationals
since you lost Quinn Fabray.

02:09.379 --> 02:11.798
No, the Cheerios
are stronger than ever.

02:11.882 --> 02:14.550
We're gonna take nationals
with this routine.

02:19.389 --> 02:23.351
Mediocre!
Hit the showers!

02:23.435 --> 02:26.521
[Chattering]
[School Bell Rings]

02:26.605 --> 02:29.816
I have several sources reporting
Quinn didn't wanna leave,

02:29.900 --> 02:32.568
but you kicked her out
because of
the pregnancy scandal.

02:32.653 --> 02:34.862
Well, Jacob,
this is Ohio,
and in order to win,

02:34.947 --> 02:37.698
my Cheerios need to appeal
to that panel of judges.

02:37.783 --> 02:40.701
So if I have a pregnant girl
doing a handspring
into a double layout,

02:40.786 --> 02:43.830
the judges aren't going
to be admiring her
impeccable form.

02:43.914 --> 02:46.624
They're going
to be wondering if
the centrifugal force...

02:46.708 --> 02:48.793
is going to make
the baby's head
start crowning.

02:48.877 --> 02:51.629
Oh, and by the way,
all this-
off the record.

02:51.713 --> 02:53.589
Probably should've
told you that earlier.

02:53.715 --> 02:55.675
This isn't fair.
Is it fair that...

02:55.759 --> 02:59.220
I have to stop
providing the baseball team
with protective cups?

02:59.304 --> 03:02.473
I only get a certain
amount of dollars a year
to spend, William.

03:02.599 --> 03:05.184
Yeah, but Artie-
He's used to
overcoming challenges.

03:05.269 --> 03:08.104
He'll just have to find
his own ride to sectionals.

03:08.188 --> 03:12.233
That "handicapable" bus
costs $600 a week to rent.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.652
We can't afford it.
But there's enough money
in the budget...

03:14.736 --> 03:17.613
to fly the Cheerios
all over the country
for their competitions?

03:17.698 --> 03:21.742
Sue Sylvester has boosters
that write fat checks.

03:21.827 --> 03:24.745
None of her travel expenses
come out of the school budget.

03:24.830 --> 03:27.540
Look. When I was in
the Glee Club,

03:27.624 --> 03:30.877
the best part
of the competitions
was the bus ride to the event.

03:30.961 --> 03:33.296
It was about camaraderie
and supporting each other.

03:33.380 --> 03:35.131
You think I feel
good about this?

03:35.215 --> 03:38.301
Well, my students
won't stand for it.

03:38.385 --> 03:41.304
That's very moving,
but my hands are tied,
Schue.

03:41.388 --> 03:45.766
If you want that bus,
you're gonna have to find
a way to pay for it yourself.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.312
[Sighs]

03:52.816 --> 03:55.318
[School Bell Rings]

03:58.113 --> 04:00.489
What about Target?
Tried. Not hiring.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.910
Another doctor bill
came to my parents' house
last night, Finn.

04:03.994 --> 04:06.913
We're lucky that I'm clever
and intercepted it.

04:06.997 --> 04:09.123
But we have to start
paying these doctors' bills,

04:09.207 --> 04:11.584
or they're gonna go
to a collection agency.

04:11.668 --> 04:15.421
And then my parents
are gonna find out that
I'm with child— your child.

04:15.505 --> 04:18.716
All right, guys.
We're doin' a new number
for sectionals.

04:18.800 --> 04:22.178
I know that pop songs
have sort of been
our signature pieces.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.513
But I did a little research
on past winners,

04:24.598 --> 04:27.475
and it turns out that
the judges like songs
that are more accessible.

04:27.559 --> 04:31.270
Stuff they know.
Uh, standards, Broadway.

04:31.355 --> 04:34.065
"Defying Gravity"?
I have an iPod shuffle...

04:34.149 --> 04:36.734
dedicated exclusively
to selections from Wicked.

04:36.818 --> 04:39.570
- This is amazing.
- Think you can handle it,
Rachel?

04:39.655 --> 04:43.532
It's my go-to shower song.
It's also my ringtone.

04:43.617 --> 04:46.410
[Mercedes]
Why do we have to go
all vanilla on this song?

04:46.495 --> 04:49.330
See, what we need
is my chocolate thunder.

04:49.414 --> 04:53.376
We don't have time to rearrange
the song for you, Mercedes.
Rachel is singing it.

04:53.460 --> 04:56.587
Don't worry. We'll find
something for you
to dip in chocolate.

04:56.672 --> 04:59.423
[Laughter]
On to item two.

04:59.508 --> 05:01.384
The school won't pay for
the special bus we need...

05:01.468 --> 05:03.511
to take Artie and his wheelchair
with us to sectionals.

05:03.595 --> 05:05.972
- Wh-Wh-What?
- That's completely unfair.

05:06.056 --> 05:10.101
So, we're gonna
have to raise money
to pay for it ourselves.

05:10.185 --> 05:14.981
See, when I was in Glee Club
and we needed new
silk cummerbunds for regionals,

05:15.065 --> 05:16.983
we held a bake sale.

05:17.067 --> 05:18.776
[Laughter]

05:18.860 --> 05:23.698
Wait. You're joking, right?
I mean, bake sales
are kind of "bougie."

05:23.782 --> 05:26.826
So hip people stopped eating
delicious sugary treats?

05:26.910 --> 05:30.579
It's not that.
It's most of us
don't know how to bake.

05:30.664 --> 05:33.124
I find recipes confusing.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.334
My family's fully
committed to takeout.

05:35.419 --> 05:38.379
Yeah, Mr. Schue.
Kids are busier
than when you went here.

05:38.463 --> 05:42.883
We've got homework and football
and teen pregnancy, lunch.

05:42.968 --> 05:44.844
Can't Artie's dad
just take him?

05:44.928 --> 05:48.222
I can't believe how insensitive
you're all being.

05:48.306 --> 05:50.558
- Are you a team?
- Of course.

05:50.642 --> 05:53.310
But Artie understands.
Don't you, Artie?

05:53.395 --> 05:56.022
Of-Of course.
It-It's cool.

05:56.106 --> 06:00.234
I mean, anything that takes away
our time from rehearsing
doesn't serve the team.

06:01.862 --> 06:04.113
[School Bell Rings]

06:11.371 --> 06:13.414
Let me help you out,
buddy.
Thank you.

06:13.498 --> 06:16.125
Hey, I'm really sorry about
how they all reacted, Artie.

06:16.209 --> 06:20.463
It's okay. I'm used to it.
They just... don't get it.
[Chuckles]

06:22.507 --> 06:25.342
Can I use the auditorium
this afternoon to rehearse,
Mr. Schue?

06:25.469 --> 06:28.345
Some of the band equipment's
in there.
Sure.

06:46.656 --> 06:49.867
