♪ I'm dancing with myself♪

09:59.766 --> 10:02.685
♪ When there's nothing to lose
and there's nothing to prove ♪

10:02.769 --> 10:04.937
♪ I'll be dancing with myself♪

10:05.021 --> 10:08.023
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪♪

10:09.901 --> 10:13.529
[Laughing]
[Whimpering Softly]

10:15.031 --> 10:17.032
[Puck]
I didn't even know
we had a home ec room.

10:17.117 --> 10:19.535
[Scoffs]
What's all this?

10:19.619 --> 10:24.039
Ingredients for cupcakes...
for the stupid bake sale.

10:29.045 --> 10:33.132
What's this?
It's what I had left over
from my pool cleaning money...

10:33.216 --> 10:36.010
after I bought dip
and nunchakus.

10:36.094 --> 10:39.179
I was getting that
you kind of need money...
for our kid.

10:39.264 --> 10:40.889
For my kid.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.935
Eighteen dollars.

10:45.020 --> 10:47.354
How much has Finn
given you?

10:48.648 --> 10:50.899
Just stop.

10:52.110 --> 10:54.069
I told you before.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.739
I don't care if that baby
comes out with a Mohawk.

10:56.823 --> 10:59.783
I will go to my grave
swearing it's Finn's.

11:06.416 --> 11:09.376
It would be pretty awesome
if it came out
with a Mohawk.

11:10.879 --> 11:13.797
[Chuckles]
You are such an egghead.

11:13.882 --> 11:16.050
I'm not.

11:26.603 --> 11:28.270
[Laughing]

11:34.569 --> 11:36.987
[Grunts Loudly]
[Squeals]
That was perfectly measured!

11:38.573 --> 11:40.532
There you go. Oh!
[Laughing]

11:40.617 --> 11:42.785
Come on. Oh!

11:49.417 --> 11:51.418
What the hell?

11:52.670 --> 11:56.465
[Chuckles]
We're baking.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.592
I can see that.

11:58.676 --> 12:01.136
I'm gonna go change.

12:06.851 --> 12:09.103
Where's my jelly cream center?

12:09.187 --> 12:11.814
Sorry, Dad.
I must've forgotten.

12:11.898 --> 12:13.816
What's up with
your brain today?

12:13.900 --> 12:16.902
You know, I think
it's goin' soft from all
that crap you put in your hair.

12:16.986 --> 12:19.655
It's organic,
and I'm fine.

12:22.117 --> 12:24.910
I'm sorry.
It's a Glee Club thing.

12:24.994 --> 12:29.331
It's not about a guy, is it?
Because I'm not ready
to have that conversation.

12:29.416 --> 12:32.000
Well, at least you
don't have to worry about
me getting someone pregnant.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.753
[Chuckling]

12:34.838 --> 12:39.716
It's not a guy.
We're doing this amazing
song for sectionals,

12:39.801 --> 12:43.637
a personal favorite of mine,
and Mr. Schuester won't
give me a chance to sing it.

12:43.763 --> 12:47.558
Why?
It's traditionally
sung by a girl.

12:47.642 --> 12:50.602
Well, you sing like a girl.
You know, in a good way.

12:50.687 --> 12:52.396
Look, Kurt.

12:52.480 --> 12:54.440
I don't know how
this music stuff works.

12:54.524 --> 12:57.776
I'm pretty exclusively committed
to my Mellencamp collection, but...

12:57.861 --> 12:59.945
isn't there more crossover
nowadays?

13:00.029 --> 13:01.947
You know,
chicks doin' construction?

13:02.031 --> 13:05.242
Guys wearin' dress shoes
with no socks?

13:05.326 --> 13:08.662
Didn't that girl
from your high school just
join the boys' wrestling team?

13:08.788 --> 13:11.248
[Whistle Blowing]
Yes! Whoo!

13:12.584 --> 13:14.835
Yes, but her parents
had to sue the school.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.591
This is really
gettin' you down,
isn't it?

13:20.675 --> 13:22.926
I'm... full of ennui.

13:24.053 --> 13:26.889
So it's...
really getting you down?

13:29.100 --> 13:31.018
Yes.

13:31.102 --> 13:33.770
You can't discriminate
against my kid
because of his sex,

13:33.855 --> 13:36.148
religion,
political affiliation,

13:36.232 --> 13:38.275
or the fact that he's queer
as a three-dollar bill.

13:38.359 --> 13:42.029
- And I won't accept it.
- This isn't academics
or athletics, Mr. Hummel.

13:42.113 --> 13:46.700
It's an arts program,
and Mr. Schuester's
judgments are subjective.

13:46.784 --> 13:48.911
You put on a blindfold
and listen to my kid sing,

13:48.995 --> 13:50.954
and you will swear
you're hearing
Ronnie Spector.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.582
Wait-
Don't try to backpedal
on this, Schuester.

13:53.666 --> 13:55.834
I was just going
to agree with you.

13:55.919 --> 13:58.462
I know this is gonna
be hard on you, Rachel,

13:58.546 --> 14:01.715
but I can't in good conscience
preach about the importance
of helping Artie,

14:01.799 --> 14:03.675
and then reject Kurt's request
out of hand.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.511
So you're giving him
my part?

14:05.595 --> 14:08.138
Now, I can’t just
give him the part.
That would be just as wrong.

14:08.223 --> 14:10.140
But I can
let him audition.

14:10.225 --> 14:14.228
What do you mean,
like a tryout?
All right, that seems fair.

14:14.312 --> 14:17.189
This is totally unfair.
You gave me the part.

14:17.273 --> 14:21.693
And I will give it
to you again if you can
sing the song better than Kurt.

14:21.778 --> 14:24.238
Okay, this seems like
a reasonable deal.

14:24.322 --> 14:26.907
But how do I know
this isn’t just some show...

14:26.991 --> 14:29.660
to stop me from takin'
a flamethrower to this place?

14:30.912 --> 14:32.704
Who's gonna judge?

14:32.789 --> 14:34.748
Now, all of you are gonna judge.

14:34.832 --> 14:39.670
And in the spirit
of full access, each of you
is going to get a vote.

14:39.754 --> 14:42.089
Whatever singer
has the most votes
gets the part.

14:42.173 --> 14:46.385
This isn't gonna be about
talent, Mr. Schuester. It's
gonna be a popularity contest.

14:46.469 --> 14:49.596
Stop right there.
Mr. Schue, if I may?

14:54.727 --> 14:57.104
We all know
I'm more popular than Rachel.

14:57.188 --> 14:59.147
And I dress better than her.

14:59.232 --> 15:03.110
But I want you all to promise me
that you're going to vote for
whoever sings the song better.

15:03.194 --> 15:05.821
Raise your right hand.

15:05.905 --> 15:08.031
Your right hand,
Brittany.

15:08.116 --> 15:10.409
It's this one.
Sorry.

15:10.493 --> 15:13.912
Repeat after me.
I promise to vote for whoever
sings the song better.

15:13.997 --> 15:18.333
I promise to vote
for whoever sings
the song better.

15:18.418 --> 15:20.627
Good luck.

15:22.046 --> 15:25.340
- It's on.
- [School Bell Rings]

15:26.843 --> 15:29.845
All right, guys.

15:33.308 --> 15:35.434
Maybe one of these days,
you'll find a way...

15:35.518 --> 15:38.854
to create teaching moments
without ruining my life.

15:47.989 --> 15:53.160
Schue, I saw all your kids
in their wheelchairs,
and I was very impressed.

15:53.244 --> 15:55.787
Well, thank you,
Principal Figgins.
But actually,

15:55.872 --> 15:58.999
it's made me realize that
there's only one wheelchair
entrance in this school,

15:59.083 --> 16:01.418
and it's all the way in
the far end of campus.

16:01.502 --> 16:03.337
McKinley needs ramps.

16:03.421 --> 16:06.632
No way. Those are
what I call "lazy makers."

16:06.716 --> 16:08.634
They discourage our
able-bodied students...

16:08.718 --> 16:10.927
from getting
their proper exercise
by using the stairs.

16:11.054 --> 16:13.347
What is she doing here?
Yes. What am I doing here?

16:13.431 --> 16:15.974
I have a Cheerios routine
to polish that's
gonna clinch us nationals.

16:16.059 --> 16:19.311
I brought you two in here
because both of you
have a point.

16:19.395 --> 16:23.940
Handicapped ramps
are expensive,
but inspiration is free.

16:24.025 --> 16:26.693
Will, I'm so inspired
by your stunt...

16:26.778 --> 16:29.529
that I'm insisting
that Miss Sylvester do
the same with the Cheerios.

16:29.614 --> 16:33.200
- I beg your pardon?
- Cheerios is not
accessible, Sue.

16:33.284 --> 16:35.202
It's by invitation only.

16:35.286 --> 16:39.831
I want to see a squad
that reflects
our community's diversity.

16:39.916 --> 16:43.377
- Now, Glee Club
held open auditions.
- And everyone got in.

16:43.461 --> 16:46.213
Now that Quinn Fabray
is off the squad,

16:46.297 --> 16:48.715
you will hold open auditions
to fill her slot.

16:48.800 --> 16:53.095
And Mr. Schuester
will monitor them to make sure
that they're fair to all.

16:53.179 --> 16:54.971
Okay, let me break
this down for you here.

16:55.056 --> 16:58.975
There comes a point when
you've gotta stop seeing people
for what they look like...

16:59.060 --> 17:01.269
and ask them to show you
what they can do.

17:01.354 --> 17:06.566
And as soon as a cheerleader
rolls herself out onto
the field in a wheelchair,

17:06.651 --> 17:10.696
she becomes
decidedly less effective
at cheering people up.

17:10.780 --> 17:12.698
- It's just a fact.
- No, Sue.

17:12.782 --> 17:17.077
The fact is, you've never
given other students the
fair shake that they deserve.

17:18.454 --> 17:20.872
I'm asking you to try it.
What do you have to lose?

17:20.957 --> 17:23.417
Maybe somebody at the school
will surprise you.

17:25.753 --> 17:30.006
Cupcake?
[Sniffs]

17:30.091 --> 17:32.175
Cupcakes suck.
That's why we're not
selling any.

17:32.260 --> 17:34.469
It's not about the cupcakes.
It's about us.

17:34.554 --> 17:36.722
Nobody wants
to buy from losers.

17:36.806 --> 17:39.599
We're in Glee Club
and in wheelchairs.

17:39.684 --> 17:41.601
She has a point.
Six months ago,

17:41.686 --> 17:43.812
I could've sold
50 of these things
on fear alone.

17:43.896 --> 17:47.816
Oh, my God.
What is she doing?

17:47.900 --> 17:50.402
I actually think
they're kind of friends.

17:50.486 --> 17:52.779
Brittany's always cheating
off her test papers
in math class.

17:52.864 --> 17:56.867
See so many?
And look how pretty
they are, Becky.

17:56.951 --> 17:58.285
Wow!

17:58.369 --> 18:00.412
Brittany, you're supposed
to be in your wheelchair.

18:00.496 --> 18:01.997
I lost it.

18:02.081 --> 18:05.333
Are you a cheerleader?
It's so cool.

18:05.418 --> 18:07.669
So is buying a cupcake.
That's really cool.

18:07.795 --> 18:11.381
But I don't have
any money.
That's okay. I have some.

18:15.178 --> 18:17.345
Thank you.

18:19.474 --> 18:21.475
Thanks.

18:22.477 --> 18:24.895
So how much
do we have now?

18:24.979 --> 18:28.273
Well, with this one dollar,
we have one dollar.

18:28.357 --> 18:30.484
This is ridiculous.

18:30.568 --> 18:34.738
- Maybe if we put a jellybean
on top, we'd sell more.
- Are you an idiot?

18:34.822 --> 18:37.574
How am I supposed
to trust you to
take care of our baby...

18:37.658 --> 18:40.118
when you can't even
figure out how
to sell a damn cupcake?

18:40.203 --> 18:42.871
- Stop attacking me.
I'm sick of it.
- Get a job.

18:42.955 --> 18:47.209
I'm trying!
Stupid wheelchair!

18:47.293 --> 18:50.170
[Sighs]

18:54.967 --> 18:56.968
I don't know
what I'm supposed
to be doing here.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.554
You just call a name.
They come in
and try out.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.556
Just give 'em a chance
to express themselves.

19:01.641 --> 19:04.684
I'm about to projectile
express myself
all over your Hush Puppies.

19:04.769 --> 19:08.480
McKinley!
Hey, hey! McKinley!

19:08.564 --> 19:10.524
- Hey, hey-
- No.

19:14.862 --> 19:17.113
No.

19:18.658 --> 19:21.076
You're not serious,
are you?

19:22.328 --> 19:25.413
Tell me you're not serious.

19:25.498 --> 19:26.998
No!

19:27.083 --> 19:28.917
No friggin' way, Jacob.

19:38.386 --> 19:39.761
Freak!

19:41.556 --> 19:43.974
Okay, I've been
at this for an hour.
That's all I promised.

19:44.058 --> 19:47.686
Sue, there's just one more
person on the list.
Give her a shot.

19:47.770 --> 19:49.771
Becky Johnson.
Jackson.

19:49.856 --> 19:52.732
Jackson.

19:54.110 --> 19:56.278
Be nice, Sue.

19:56.362 --> 19:59.322
I heard that you do
a routine with jump ropes.

19:59.407 --> 20:01.449
I wanted to show you
what I could do.

20:13.421 --> 20:15.463
Becky, I'm gonna
stop you right there.

20:17.133 --> 20:22.429
You're in.
Be at practice tomorrow
at 4:00 p.m. Congratulations.

20:27.310 --> 20:30.562
What are you
up to, Sue?
I'm just following orders, Will.

20:30.646 --> 20:34.733
I'm doing what I was told.
And I found myself
a brand-new Cheerio.

20:34.817 --> 20:37.152
You're up to something.

20:37.236 --> 20:40.155
I don't like this,
Sue.

20:41.198 --> 20:43.074
[Sighs]
[School Bell Rings]

20:43.159 --> 20:47.579
I'm just saying,
she has a point.
You are kind of an idiot.

20:47.663 --> 20:49.998
Nice support, dude.
Whatever happened to
"bros before ho's"?

20:50.082 --> 20:53.335
You've got a baby on the way,
bro, and you haven't
done spit to take care of it.

20:53.461 --> 20:55.921
Like you'd do
any different?
Damn straight.

20:56.005 --> 20:58.089
How?
Nobody's hiring.

20:58.174 --> 21:00.175
Sell your Xbox.
Rob a bank.

21:00.259 --> 21:03.845
Go all Robin Hood
on this joint.
Whatever it takes.

21:03.930 --> 21:08.975
All I ever hear is you whining
and crying about how hard
this is on you. What about her?

21:09.060 --> 21:12.062
Dude, you are so out of line.
You don't know what
I'm dealing with.

21:12.146 --> 21:15.732
All I know is that you're
a punk who doesn't deserve
to have Quinn as his girlfriend!

21:15.816 --> 21:17.359
You're a punk!

21:22.031 --> 21:24.699
- [Finn Groans Loudly]
- [Gasping, Chattering]

21:27.995 --> 21:30.830
Hey, hey!
Break it up!
Break it up!

21:30.915 --> 21:33.500
- Come on! Hey-
- He started it!

21:33.584 --> 21:36.753
- I don't care! Now.
- [Pants]

21:36.837 --> 21:42.008
You-You guys are best friends.
What the hell's goin' on?

21:42.093 --> 21:44.970
I'm just really stressed
about the bake sale.

21:45.054 --> 21:47.305
I really like Artie, okay?

21:49.725 --> 21:51.726
You okay?

21:58.234 --> 22:01.945
The key to a double turn
is to just go for it.

22:02.029 --> 22:04.322
You push with the right wheel,
and pull as hard as you can
with the left...

22:04.407 --> 22:07.784
and find a spot on the wall
to spot you
so you don't get dizzy.

22:07.868 --> 22:10.412
Whoo!

22:14.291 --> 22:16.584
[Will]
Okay, guys.
Uh, take five, all right?

22:16.669 --> 22:19.713
Oh! Remember to
show up early on Thursday.

22:19.797 --> 22:22.298
It's Rachel versus Kurt
for the big solo.

22:22.383 --> 22:24.759
[Students Gasping,
Chuckling]

22:26.095 --> 22:29.764
Careful.
Respect the chair.

22:34.186 --> 22:36.813
I really admire you, Artie.

22:36.897 --> 22:39.274
I had no idea
how difficult this was.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.942
It's just like you
with your stutter.

22:41.027 --> 22:43.737
You don't really
notice it
after a while.

22:45.322 --> 22:47.949
H-H-How did it happen?

22:48.034 --> 22:49.951
You don't talk about it.

22:50.036 --> 22:53.747
My mom and I got in
a really bad car accident
when I was eight.

22:53.831 --> 22:57.375
And she was fine,
but I've been in
the chair ever since.

22:57.460 --> 23:00.879
But I wanna be
very clear.

23:00.963 --> 23:03.089
I still have the use
of my penis.

23:06.469 --> 23:08.261
[Softly]
Oh, God.

23:24.487 --> 23:27.030
♪♪ [Singing Notes]

23:27.114 --> 23:29.115
♪♪ [Continues:
Raising Pitch]

23:31.827 --> 23:33.745
♪♪ [Continues]
[Phone Ringing]

23:33.829 --> 23:36.164
Excuse me a second.

23:36.248 --> 23:38.249
♪♪ [Continues]

23:40.002 --> 23:42.003
[Ringing Continues]

23:45.299 --> 23:47.634
♪♪ [Continues: Raising Pitch]

23:47.718 --> 23:50.845
Hummel Tires and Lube.
Yep. Who's this?

23:53.474 --> 23:55.391
[Man]
Your son's a fag.

23:55.476 --> 23:57.477
[Line Clicks, Dial Tone]

23:59.230 --> 24:01.231
[Beeps]

24:02.942 --> 24:06.486
Hey, Dad.
What the hell is wrong
with this machine?

24:06.570 --> 24:08.613
I hit it— the high "F."

24:08.697 --> 24:10.657
The magical note I need
for "Defying Gravity."

24:10.783 --> 24:12.951
I hit it.
It means I'm gonna win.
That's great.

24:13.035 --> 24:15.829
Good for you.
Just how long until
the damn coffee's ready?

24:15.913 --> 24:18.373
What's going on?

24:18.457 --> 24:21.584
I got a phone call
this morning.
The anonymous kind.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.505
It was some dude telling me
my son was a fag.

24:25.589 --> 24:30.093
Oh. Well,
that's not a big deal.
I get that all the time.

24:30.177 --> 24:32.011
Yeah, but I don't.

24:32.096 --> 24:34.514
Now, look, Kurt.

24:34.598 --> 24:37.016
I try to do right by you.
You know, open some doors.

24:37.101 --> 24:39.769
What father wouldn't
do that for his kid?
And I know it's good for you...

24:39.854 --> 24:42.856
to be out there with—
with all this Glee Club stuff.

24:42.940 --> 24:46.860
I just- I don't
want you to get hurt.

24:48.112 --> 24:50.822
So you don't want me
to audition for the solo?

24:50.906 --> 24:52.824
No, no.
Let me be clear, all right?

24:52.908 --> 24:56.452
No one pushes
the Hummels around,
especially cowards on the phone.

25:00.916 --> 25:04.002
Sometimes, I just—
I wish your mom
was still around, you know?

25:04.086 --> 25:06.546
She was better at,

25:06.630 --> 25:09.007
you know,
handlin' this kind of thing.

25:09.091 --> 25:11.050
You know, handlin' me.

25:13.888 --> 25:15.805
Look, congrats on, uh,

25:15.890 --> 25:18.308
you know, the cool "A"
or the high "C" or, you know,
whatever it was.

25:18.434 --> 25:20.935
High "F."
Yeah.

25:29.069 --> 25:31.779
There's your problem.
You just had
a bent push rim.

25:33.657 --> 25:36.659
Good as new.
Thanks, Finn.

25:36.744 --> 25:39.412
You're the only one who was
willing to help me.

25:39.538 --> 25:42.957
I'm really nervous about
the "diva off" tomorrow.
Don't be.

25:43.042 --> 25:45.627
You know,
I don't wanna win
out of charity.

25:45.711 --> 25:47.921
I wanna win the solo
because it's right
for the club.

25:48.005 --> 25:49.923
I really think that
the judges at sectionals...

25:50.007 --> 25:54.260
will find a female version
of "Defying Gravity"
much more accessible.

25:54.345 --> 25:58.431
But... I don't think
that's gonna happen.

25:58.515 --> 26:00.433
People just don't
like me.

26:00.517 --> 26:03.311
Yeah, you might wanna
work on that.

26:04.855 --> 26:07.482
I like you.

26:09.193 --> 26:12.028
- We need to talk.
- I'll get out of your way.

26:12.112 --> 26:14.864
Nope! You stay.
I need a witness.
Do you know what this is?

26:14.949 --> 26:17.742
Oh. It's just
a "past due" notice.
My mom gets 'em all the time.

26:17.826 --> 26:20.453
Right. But if this
sonogram bill doesn't get paid,

26:20.537 --> 26:22.455
it's not your phone
that's gonna get cut off.

26:22.539 --> 26:24.457
You will get cut off.

26:24.541 --> 26:26.292
You need to help me
with this, Finn,

26:26.377 --> 26:29.128
or else we're gonna go
our separate ways.

26:32.299 --> 26:34.801
[Sighs]
I'm screwed.

26:36.387 --> 26:38.388
Not necessarily.

26:44.645 --> 26:46.646
[Chattering]

26:47.731 --> 26:49.607
I know. I know.
I know, I know.

26:49.733 --> 26:52.819
Hey. Hey, guys.
Hey, guys, this is amazing.
[Girl] Hi.

26:52.903 --> 26:56.823
Puck found his Nana Connie's
old recipe. They're addictive.
Do you want one?

26:56.907 --> 27:00.076
No. No, thanks.
I don't wanna take one away
from a paying customer.

27:00.202 --> 27:01.953
Yeah, I know.
Sure.
Hey, uh—

27:02.037 --> 27:04.455
Nice work, buddy.

27:04.540 --> 27:06.541
These are so good.

27:06.625 --> 27:08.876
[Puck Narrating]
This isn't Nana Connie's
old recipe.

27:08.961 --> 27:11.212
She couldn't cook at all.
She was a diabetic.

27:11.297 --> 27:14.173
So the only sweets
she had in her house
was dried fruit.

27:15.551 --> 27:18.803
I knew I had to do something
to help Quinn out with our baby.

27:18.887 --> 27:22.307
I don't know what kind of stuff
you need for a baby
that's still in your stomach.

27:22.391 --> 27:24.892
Bottles, diapers—
That kind of thing, I guess.

27:24.977 --> 27:28.646
But my baby mama
was gonna get it all.

27:28.731 --> 27:33.026
To make sure that happened,
I used the two things
I know the most about—

27:33.110 --> 27:34.902
lying and crime.

27:34.987 --> 27:37.155
Is there a lot
of pain, Noah?

27:37.239 --> 27:40.199
[Mock Sobbing]
The doctor said the shark
fractured my spinal cord.

27:40.284 --> 27:42.577
This is why I don't
go to the aquarium.

27:42.661 --> 27:47.498
I'm going to give you
as much as you want,
20 cents on the dollar.

27:47.583 --> 27:50.251
[Puck Narrating]
I don't put in enough
to get you hallucinatin'.

27:50.336 --> 27:52.795
Just enough to give you
a wicked case of the munchies.

27:52.921 --> 27:55.882
That's why they keep
coming back for more.
Yeah.

27:55.966 --> 27:58.634
See? I told you
I'd make a great dad.

27:59.762 --> 28:03.097
Faster. Harder!

28:04.725 --> 28:07.810
Those better be
tears of joy, Becky.

28:07.895 --> 28:10.355
Faster! Harder!

28:10.439 --> 28:12.899
Okay, stop.
[Sighs]

28:12.983 --> 28:15.360
Becky, this is terrible.

28:15.444 --> 28:18.071
I've tried, Coach.
This is really hard.

28:18.155 --> 28:20.823
You think this is hard?
Try auditioning for Baywatch...

28:20.908 --> 28:22.825
and being told that they're
going in another direction.

28:22.910 --> 28:25.328
That was hard.
Hit the showers.

28:25.412 --> 28:28.414
Thanks, Coach.
[Giggles]

28:35.672 --> 28:37.673
Hi.

28:41.053 --> 28:42.970
Sue, you are unbelievable.

28:43.055 --> 28:45.056
And you are
a terrible spy.

28:45.140 --> 28:48.643
You might try breathing
through your nose sometime.
If you were a sniper,

28:48.727 --> 28:51.729
I'd have already
radioed in your coordinates,
just like in the Falklands.

28:51.855 --> 28:54.732
I'm not gonna let you
bully that girl, Sue.
Oh, I bully everybody, Will.

28:54.858 --> 28:56.901
It's the way I roll.
Yeah, but this is different.

28:56.985 --> 28:58.903
She's not like
everybody else.

28:58.987 --> 29:01.239
I want you to listen
to what you just said,
William.

29:01.323 --> 29:03.950
You're asking me
to treat this girl differently
because she has a disability,

29:04.034 --> 29:07.078
when actually, it seems to me
she just wants to be treated
like everybody else.

29:07.204 --> 29:11.082
Why are you doing this?
Because I know you,
and you're up to something.

29:11.166 --> 29:14.710
You don't know
the first thing about me.

29:19.591 --> 29:22.218
[Door Closes]

29:25.848 --> 29:29.559
Good luck.
I'm rooting for you.

29:32.855 --> 29:38.693
All right.
Welcome to the Glee Club's
first official "diva off."

29:38.777 --> 29:42.363
- [Applause]
- Let's get this party started!

29:47.119 --> 29:48.870
♪♪ [Piano]

29:53.917 --> 29:57.044
♪ Something has changed
within me ♪

29:57.129 --> 29:59.672
♪ Something
is not the same ♪

29:59.756 --> 30:03.551
♪ I'm through with
playing by the rules ♪

30:03.635 --> 30:06.262
♪ Of someone else's game ♪

30:06.346 --> 30:09.640
♪ Too late for second-guessing ♪

30:09.725 --> 30:12.351
♪ Too late to go back to sleep ♪

30:12.436 --> 30:15.897
♪ It's time to trust
my instincts ♪

30:15.981 --> 30:19.358
♪ Close my eyes and leap ♪

30:19.443 --> 30:21.652
♪ It's time to try ♪

30:21.737 --> 30:25.323
♪ Defying gravity ♪

30:25.407 --> 30:27.825
♪ I think I'll try ♪

30:27.910 --> 30:31.662
♪ Defying gravity ♪

30:31.747 --> 30:34.081
♪ Kiss me good-bye ♪

30:34.166 --> 30:37.460
♪ I'm defying gravity ♪

30:37.544 --> 30:41.088
♪ And you won't
bring me down ♪

30:46.053 --> 30:49.096
♪ I'm through accepting limits ♪

30:49.181 --> 30:51.891
♪ 'Cause someone says
they're so ♪

30:51.975 --> 30:54.560
♪ There's some things
I cannot change ♪

30:54.645 --> 30:58.189
♪ But till I try
I'll never know ♪

30:58.273 --> 31:01.192
♪ Too long I've been afraid ♪

31:01.276 --> 31:04.570
♪ Of losing love
I guess I've lost ♪

31:04.655 --> 31:11.077
♪ Well, if that’s love
it comes at much
too high a cost ♪

31:11.161 --> 31:13.663
♪ I'd sooner buy ♪

31:13.747 --> 31:17.041
♪ Defying gravity ♪

31:17.125 --> 31:19.835
♪ Kiss me good-bye ♪

31:19.920 --> 31:23.464
♪ I'm defying gravity ♪

31:23.549 --> 31:26.259
♪ I think I'll try ♪

31:26.343 --> 31:29.637
♪ Defying gravity ♪

31:29.721 --> 31:33.266
♪ And you won't
bring me down ♪

31:33.350 --> 31:35.685
♪ I'd sooner buy ♪

31:35.769 --> 31:39.397
♪ Defying gravity ♪

31:39.481 --> 31:42.066
♪ Kiss me good-bye ♪

31:42.150 --> 31:45.778
♪ I'm defying gravity ♪

31:45.862 --> 31:48.364
♪ I think I'll try ♪

31:48.448 --> 31:51.742
♪ Defying gravity ♪

31:51.827 --> 31:55.871
[Off-key]
♪ And you won't
bring me down ♪

31:55.956 --> 31:59.333
♪ Bring me down ♪

31:59.418 --> 32:04.630
♪♪ [Vocalizing]

32:04.715 --> 32:04.839
♪♪ [Ends]

32:04.840 --> 32:05.047
♪♪ [Ends]

32:05.048 --> 32:06.674
♪♪ [Ends]

32:09.303 --> 32:11.304
[Applause]

32:12.764 --> 32:14.974
[Will]
Good job, Kurt. Good job.

32:15.058 --> 32:17.059
[School Bell Rings]

32:19.229 --> 32:21.564
Hey, wait up.

32:21.648 --> 32:26.027
I cracked open the piggy bank.
It's for you.
Well, it's for "it."

32:26.111 --> 32:28.321
"It" is a she.

32:29.781 --> 32:32.575
Cool. I told you
I wasn't a deadbeat.

32:32.659 --> 32:35.578
Look, Puck, this is
really sweet, but-

32:35.662 --> 32:37.663
I can get more.

32:38.915 --> 32:41.500
People call me a screwup
because...

32:41.585 --> 32:43.628
I think school's for suckers.

32:43.712 --> 32:46.297
But I got ambition.

32:46.381 --> 32:51.844
Get us a house,
some stuff, furniture.
We could be a family.

32:53.847 --> 32:55.931
Finn is
your best friend.

32:56.016 --> 32:57.933
He'd be pissed for a while.

32:58.018 --> 33:02.605
But then he'd realize he doesn't
have to deal with all this.
He'd bake me a damn cake.

33:02.689 --> 33:04.690
You stole from
the cupcake fund.

33:04.775 --> 33:07.068
No, I didn't.

33:07.152 --> 33:09.737
[Sighs]
Fine. I did.

33:09.821 --> 33:11.947
I made all those cupcakes.

33:12.032 --> 33:15.076
I'm all about
being a team player,
but my family comes first.

33:16.828 --> 33:21.791
I get it.
And... I'm sorry.

33:21.875 --> 33:25.795
I should've never
called you a Lima loser.
You're not.

33:25.879 --> 33:30.591
You're special
and romantic...

33:30.676 --> 33:34.178
and a good enough person
to realize that...

33:34.262 --> 33:36.889
we are not gonna
take money from a friend
in a wheelchair.

33:38.350 --> 33:40.059
Hey.

33:43.772 --> 33:45.606
Here.

33:45.732 --> 33:48.693
What's this?
I got a job.

33:48.777 --> 33:51.320
Excuse me.

33:51.405 --> 33:52.988
- Are you the manager?
- Yes.

33:53.073 --> 33:55.700
You need to hire my friend Finn.
He is clearly "handicapable,"

33:55.784 --> 33:58.828
and refusing to hire him
could be seen
as discrimination.

33:58.912 --> 34:01.455
My dads are gay.
And unless you want
the full force...

34:01.540 --> 34:03.624
of the American Civil
Liberties Union
coming down on you,

34:03.709 --> 34:06.711
I'd work something out.

34:06.795 --> 34:09.505
Gonna need to stay
in my wheelchair
as long as I'm working there.

34:09.589 --> 34:11.841
But... screw it.
It's worth it.

34:13.051 --> 34:16.095
Can I give you
a lift to rehearsal?

34:24.396 --> 34:26.480
[School Bell Rings]

34:29.693 --> 34:32.445
1, 200 bucks.
That's enough for
the short bus...

34:32.529 --> 34:34.530
and two cases
of Natty light
for the ride home.

34:34.614 --> 34:37.950
Ah. Dream on, brother.
[Applause]

34:38.034 --> 34:39.952
[Sighs]

34:40.036 --> 34:42.163
I'm very proud
of you guys.

34:44.499 --> 34:46.751
Artie.

34:46.835 --> 34:48.753
Why don't you bring this
to Principal Figgins yourself.

34:48.837 --> 34:52.631
- All right, Artie.
- [Girl] Go, Artie!

34:54.801 --> 34:59.430
- What's wrong, dude?
- I really appreciate what
you guys did for me.

34:59.514 --> 35:02.725
But I'm not the only kid
in a wheelchair at this school.

35:02.809 --> 35:05.895
And I'm sure there'll be others
after I graduate.

35:05.979 --> 35:09.607
And I know how important it is
for all of us
to go to sectionals together,

35:09.691 --> 35:12.401
but I think I'd rather
just get a ride from my dad...

35:12.486 --> 35:15.738
and use this
for a handicap ramp
in the auditorium.

35:17.449 --> 35:19.033
Any objections?

35:19.117 --> 35:21.994
Well, it sure beats having
to carry him in every day.

35:27.125 --> 35:30.544
You think she has a brain tumor?
That can cause erratic behavior.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.881
All I know is that
she walked in unannounced,

35:33.965 --> 35:37.885
and she wrote me a check
for three new
handicap ramps.

35:37.969 --> 35:41.555
I just don't get it.
I mean, first,
putting Becky in Cheerios.

35:41.640 --> 35:44.183
Now this.
What is her angle?

35:44.267 --> 35:48.562
Why ask why?
Just enjoy the fact that you're
getting your bus after all.

35:52.484 --> 35:55.069
How's she doing?
Great.

35:55.153 --> 35:58.739
She asks about you.
She's been watching you on TV.

35:58.824 --> 36:00.908
I need to get here
more often.

36:00.992 --> 36:02.910
Oh, you get here plenty.

36:02.994 --> 36:05.496
[Knocking]
Jean?

36:05.580 --> 36:07.456
Your little sister's here
to see you.

36:07.582 --> 36:09.333
Hey, Sue!
Hi, honey!

36:09.417 --> 36:12.336
- My sister's famous!
- You got that right.

36:12.420 --> 36:14.630
I got something for you.

36:14.714 --> 36:16.674
What's this?

36:16.800 --> 36:20.177
Wow! A pom-pom.
Thank you.
That's for you.

36:20.262 --> 36:23.180
- What do you feel
like doing today?
- Can we read today?

36:23.265 --> 36:25.641
- Look what I have.
- Little Red Riding Hood.

36:25.725 --> 36:27.476
Right.
Your favorite book.

36:27.561 --> 36:28.936
Wanna start
at the beginning?

36:29.062 --> 36:30.688
Yes.
All right.

36:30.814 --> 36:33.315
You ready?
Ready.

36:38.947 --> 36:42.241
[Chuckles]

36:42.325 --> 36:45.953
"Once upon a time,

36:46.037 --> 36:49.790
"there was a little girl
who lived in the forest.

36:49.875 --> 36:54.753
"Whenever she went out,
the little girl wore
a red riding cloak.

36:54.838 --> 36:59.508
So everyone in the village
called her
Little Red Riding Hood."

36:59.634 --> 37:01.468
Right?
Right.

37:01.553 --> 37:02.469
[Laughter]

37:02.470 --> 37:04.013
[Laughter]

37:04.139 --> 37:08.851
Oh, no! Oh, you're
so much faster!
You can't keep up.

37:08.935 --> 37:11.854
I can't!
This is so hard— No!

37:11.938 --> 37:15.441
[Groans]
No, this wasn't fair. You've
had eight years of practice.

37:15.525 --> 37:18.903
Excelling at
wheelchair races
is about my only advantage.

37:18.987 --> 37:23.657
It's like your stutter.
It's mostly
just a big hassle.

37:23.742 --> 37:27.745
This has been
a really fun date.

37:27.829 --> 37:30.539
But... I wanna
get out of this chair.

37:30.624 --> 37:31.999
Why?

37:32.083 --> 37:37.296
So... I can do this.

37:49.351 --> 37:51.727
I have to
tell you something.

37:51.811 --> 37:54.897
I've been faking it.

37:54.981 --> 37:56.732
Faking what?

37:56.816 --> 37:58.692
I don't have a stutter.

37:59.903 --> 38:03.614
I pretended to have one
in sixth grade because...

38:03.698 --> 38:07.409
I didn't wanna give a speech
on the Missouri Compromise.

38:07.494 --> 38:09.745
I was really shy.

38:09.829 --> 38:14.166
And it made people think
I was weird,
so they left me alone.

38:14.250 --> 38:18.128
And it wasn't until
I joined Glee Club
that I realized...

38:18.213 --> 38:21.674
how much I was missing.

38:21.758 --> 38:24.802
I don't wanna push
people away anymore.

38:24.886 --> 38:26.887
You understand what
that's like, don't you?

38:26.972 --> 38:29.723
No. I don't.

38:31.142 --> 38:33.060
I would never try
to push people away,

38:33.144 --> 38:35.062
'cause being in a chair
kind of does that for you.

38:36.690 --> 38:40.442
I thought we had something
really important in common.

38:42.862 --> 38:46.198
Wait.
Artie, I'm sorry.

38:46.282 --> 38:49.827
I am too.
I'm sorry now
you get to be normal,

38:49.911 --> 38:52.997
and I'm gonna be
stuck in this chair
the rest of my life.

38:53.081 --> 38:56.250
And that's not something
I can fake.

39:01.381 --> 39:03.716
