Hey, Dad.

39:03.842 --> 39:05.801
What are you doing?
I'm makin' biscuits.

39:05.885 --> 39:07.970
What does it look like
I'm doing?
How'd the tryout go?

39:09.389 --> 39:11.432
They gave the part
to Rachel.

39:11.516 --> 39:13.434
I knew they were
gonna rig it!

39:13.518 --> 39:16.103
I'm goin' down to that school
and I'm talkin' to Schuester.

39:16.187 --> 39:18.272
I blew the note.

39:19.315 --> 39:21.025
I wanted to lose.

39:21.109 --> 39:25.070
Kurt, I stuck my neck out
for you, and you go
and you throw the game?

39:28.825 --> 39:31.243
Dad.

39:31.327 --> 39:34.038
I've known who I was
since I was five.

39:34.122 --> 39:37.750
I adapted.
Being different
made me stronger.

39:39.669 --> 39:42.838
At the end of the day,
it's what's gonna get me
out of this cow town.

39:42.922 --> 39:44.840
You never had
to do that.

39:44.924 --> 39:47.009
I can handle myself
just fine.

39:47.093 --> 39:50.471
No, you can't.
Not about this.

39:52.098 --> 39:54.850
That phone call yesterday
was just the beginning,

39:54.934 --> 39:58.270
